description: This data file indicates the estimated number of uninsured individuals ages 19-25 in each U.S. county.  These individuals may be eligible to join their parents health plan if that plan offers dependent coverage.  The data is based on the 2007 Small Area Health Insurance Estimates (SAHIE) and March 2008 Current Population Survey Annual Social and Economic Supplement (CPS-ASEC).
